text: Astara is a raion in southeastern Azerbaijan. It was formed in 1930. There are 95,300 people. Astarachay and Tangarud rivers are in the raion. A part of the Hirkan National Park is in Astara raion. Astara is a major source for Azerbaijan's fishing industry. ==References== Category:Districts of Azerbaijan Category:Lankaran Economic Region
title: Astara District
